  "market_context": "NQ 1-minute chart on Nov 1, 2023 around 10:15–10:40 EST. Price was consolidating after a rally, then made an aggressive displacement out of and back into the range, signaling a manipulation phase within the AMD framework.",
  "key_observation": "The consolidation bodies define the box; the aggressive move out and back into the range qualifies as manipulation. Projecting the manipulation leg, the -1 standard deviation aligned precisely with the start of an existing fair value gap, providing a high-confluence target.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the consolidation phase and marked the box using the candle bodies as range boundaries.",
    "Step 2: Observed an aggressive displacement out of the range followed by aggressive displacement back into the range, qualifying as the manipulation/deviation.",
    "Step 3: Defined the entry at the retest of the deviation (top of the consolidation bodies), with stop placed on the manipulation high.",
    "Step 4: Projected the manipulation leg from the manipulation high down to the swing low that originated the move using standard deviation tool.",
    "Step 5: Noted that the -1 standard deviation projection lined up perfectly with the start of a downside fair value gap, set as the target.",
    "Step 6: Mentioned an alternative confirmation entry: wait for a down-close candle into the deviation area to be closed over, validating an order block for a tighter entry with stop on the OB low.",
    "Step 7: Let price play out — it delivered down into the fair value gap and reached the -1 standard deviation target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade worked as planned — price displaced lower into the fair value gap, hitting the -1 standard deviation target.",
  "lessons": "The Box setup pairs powerfully with AMD and standard deviation projections: use consolidation bodies as the box, enter on the retest of the manipulation deviation, and target standard deviation levels that align with fair value gaps for high-confluence exits.",
